Melt butter in large skillet on medium heat. Add carrots and onion; cook and stir 5 minutes or until tender-crisp. Stir in raisins, juices, sugar, salt, thyme, cinnamon and cardamom. Reduce heat to low; cover. Simmer 10 minutes. Stir in rice and apples; cook until thoroughly heated. Sprinkle with pine nuts just before serving.